<br />

<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
  <a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEgj2u07ZRnq0fmxYIdvq-Poy961osPCA7HBv0CmfWJAW6xVWrvMvz1n42C-kv3nLt2-7p8xn9wpPXSq99A090xuR88IGD1bnFmtsmdfNYufBJwqDIwpUwiO-JhTIKpH8lJcq2IAU1jNIGDqX8uQ-viAhzk98ranCLQ-irgjcd8XjRia3s6NDQ=s3520" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;">
    <img alt="bookstore-2021" border="0" data-original-height="2651" data-original-width="3520" height="301" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEgj2u07ZRnq0fmxYIdvq-Poy961osPCA7HBv0CmfWJAW6xVWrvMvz1n42C-kv3nLt2-7p8xn9wpPXSq99A090xuR88IGD1bnFmtsmdfNYufBJwqDIwpUwiO-JhTIKpH8lJcq2IAU1jNIGDqX8uQ-viAhzk98ranCLQ-irgjcd8XjRia3s6NDQ=w400-h301" width="400" />
  </a>
</div>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: center;">
  <i>
    "The typical, or median, American adult read five books during 2021."<br />
  </i>
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; text-align: center;">
  <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/zacharysmith/2022/01/07/sales-are-up-nearly-9-for-print-books-but-whos-reading-them/" style="color: #b4445c;" target="_blank">
    <span style="font-size: medium;">Forbes</span>
  </a>
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;"><br />Of the five books you may have read in 2021, it is likely that not all were career-oriented. Of the few that were, some offered more value than others. Let me help you decide which business books are most likely to add value to your career. These are not my opinions. These are the opinions of business experts. These are the opinions of readers who have read these books.</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  For the 14th year in a row Beantown Web has conducted a quasi-scientific meta-search to identify the best business books published during the calendar year. This year's search began by identifying 16 "Best of" lists. This resource list is available upon request. The final results are presented here.
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  A total of 222 unique books were mentioned on at least one "Best of" list. Among the unique books, 175 were mentioned only once and 47 received multiple recommendations.</p>

<h3 style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;">
  The Honorable Mention Shelf
</h3>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  Of the 47 multiple recommendations, 31 books were mentioned on two lists. These books comprise the <b>Honorable Mention</b> list.
</p>

<h3 style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;">
  The Must-Read Shelf
</h3>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  Of the 16 remaining book recommendations, nine were mentioned on three lists. These books comprise the <b>Must-Read</b>&nbsp;list:</p>

<ul style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  <li>
